79 Come le pecorelle escon del chiuso 80 a una, a due, a tre, e l’altre stanno 81 timidette atterrando l’occhio e ’l muso;
82 e ciò che fa la prima, e l’altre fanno, 83 addossandosi a lei, s’ella s’arresta, 84 semplici e quete, e lo ’mperché non sanno;
85 sì vid’ io muovere a venir la testa 86 di quella mandra fortunata allotta, 87 pudica in faccia e ne l’andare onesta.

query.result:
79 Like the little sheep go out of the enclosure 80 one at a time, two at a time, three at a time, and the others stay 81 timidly lowering the eye and the muzzle;
82 and what the first does, the others do, 83 leaning on her, if she stops, 84 simple and quiet, and the reason they do not know;
85 so I saw the head move to come 86 of that fortunate mare allotta, 87 modest in face and in the going honest.

94 Without your question I confess to you  
95 that this is a human body that you see;  
96 for which the light of the sun on earth is feeble.

109 When I was humbly disavowed  
110 of never having seen him, he said: “Now see”;  
111 and showed me a wound at the top of the chest.

121 Horrible were my sins;  
122 but infinite goodness has such great arms,  
123 that takes what is turned to it.

